&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2020.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The WHO Foundation recently collaborated with Novo Nordisk to address childhood obesity in India.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Establishment:&lt;/strong&gt; The WHO Foundation was created in &lt;strong&gt;May 2020&lt;/strong&gt; as an independent entity.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Headquarters:&lt;/strong&gt; It is based in &lt;strong&gt;Geneva, Switzerland&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Purpose:&lt;/strong&gt; It was established to facilitate &lt;strong&gt;private sector and individual donations&lt;/strong&gt; to support the World Health Organization&amp;#39;s mission, as WHO itself cannot directly accept certain types of private funding.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Independence:&lt;/strong&gt; Although it supports WHO&amp;#39;s goals, it is legally independent of the World Health Organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;World Health Organization (WHO)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Established on &lt;strong&gt;April 7, 1948&lt;/strong&gt;, it is a specialized agency of the United Nations responsible for international public health.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Ayushman Bharat Sangeet&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The collaboration focuses on the &lt;strong&gt;Ayushman Bharat School Health and Wellness Programme&lt;/strong&gt;, which aims to provide holistic healthcare to school children across India.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;₹1 Trillion.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Indian government is planning a fund exceeding ₹1 trillion to expand the semiconductor ecosystem in the country.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Objective:&lt;/strong&gt; To transform India into a global semiconductor hub and compete with leaders like &lt;strong&gt;Taiwan and South Korea&lt;/strong&gt; by 2032.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fund Scope:&lt;/strong&gt; The initiative provides subsidies for &lt;strong&gt;chip design&lt;/strong&gt;, manufacturing equipment, and local supply chain growth.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preceding Scheme:&lt;/strong&gt; This follows the successful &lt;strong&gt;$10 billion (approx ₹76,000 crore)&lt;/strong&gt; incentive program launched in 2021.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Players:&lt;/strong&gt; Major companies like &lt;strong&gt;Micron Technology&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;Tata Group&lt;/strong&gt; have already initiated projects in Gujarat under previous incentives.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Economic Shift:&lt;/strong&gt; The fund aims to capitalize on India&amp;#39;s talent; currently, &lt;strong&gt;Apple Inc.&lt;/strong&gt; already assembles 25% of its iPhones in India.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Semiconductor Significance&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Chips are the &amp;quot;brain&amp;quot; of modern electronics, used in everything from smartphones and EVs to medical devices and defense systems.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Viksit Bharat @2047&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Building a self-reliant semiconductor industry is a cornerstone of India&amp;#39;s vision to become a developed nation by 2047.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Indian Banks&amp;rsquo; Association (IBA).&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Indian Banks&amp;rsquo; Association (IBA) organized a one-day conclave focused on the transformation of Regional Rural Banks (RRBs).&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Guidance:&lt;/strong&gt; The conclave was held under the direction of the &lt;strong&gt;Department of Financial Services (DFS)&lt;/strong&gt;, Ministry of Finance.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Objective:&lt;/strong&gt; To create a roadmap for next-generation reforms that align RRBs with the national goal of &lt;strong&gt;Viksit Bharat @2047&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Focus Areas:&lt;/strong&gt; Key discussions revolved around &lt;strong&gt;Digital Transformation&lt;/strong&gt;, Innovation in &lt;strong&gt;Agri-Financing&lt;/strong&gt;, and Financial Inclusion.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Human Resources:&lt;/strong&gt; A major theme was &lt;strong&gt;Capacity Building&lt;/strong&gt; to ensure RRB staff are equipped for modern banking challenges.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Regional Rural Banks (RRBs)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Established under the &lt;strong&gt;RRB Act, 1976&lt;/strong&gt;, to provide credit to small farmers, agricultural labourers, and artisans in rural areas.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;IBA&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Formed in 1946, it is a representative body of management of banking in India, operating in Mumbai.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Viksit Bharat @2047&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The Government of India&amp;#39;s vision to transform the country into a developed nation by the 100th year of independence.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;180.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Ministry of Railways reached a milestone of 180 redeveloped stations under the Amrit Bharat Station Scheme, including 8 additions in the last month.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Scope of Scheme:&lt;/strong&gt; A total of &lt;strong&gt;1,337 stations&lt;/strong&gt; have been identified for redevelopment under this initiative.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Amenities:&lt;/strong&gt; The scheme focuses on modernizing buildings and adding &lt;strong&gt;lifts, escalators, Foot Over Bridges (FOBs)&lt;/strong&gt;, and specialized facilities for &lt;strong&gt;Divyangjan&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Budgetary Growth:&lt;/strong&gt; The Gross Budgetary Allocation for Railways has grown nearly &lt;strong&gt;8 times&lt;/strong&gt; since 2014, reaching &lt;strong&gt;₹2,52,200 crore&lt;/strong&gt; in FY 2025&amp;ndash;26.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Regional Progress:&lt;/strong&gt; The latest 8 stations include locations in Kerala (Angamali, Ferok, Nilambur Road, Tripunithura), Madhya Pradesh (Chhindwara), Tamil Nadu (Mambalam), Andhra Pradesh (Nidadavolu), and Telangana (Ramagundam).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Amrit Bharat Station Scheme&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Launched in 2023, it aims at the continuous development of stations with a long-term approach, including multi-modal integration and sustainable infrastructure.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Divyangjan Facilities&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Includes tactile flooring, low-height counters, wheelchair-accessible toilets, and ramps to ensure inclusive travel.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Madhya Pradesh.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Oil India Limited (OIL) has partnered with the National Scheduled Tribes Finance and Development Corporation (NSTFDC) to improve health facilities in Madhya Pradesh.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Target Area:&lt;/strong&gt; The project specifically focuses on the &lt;strong&gt;Rajgarh district&lt;/strong&gt; of Madhya Pradesh, which is an &lt;strong&gt;Aspirational District&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Financial Commitment:&lt;/strong&gt; OIL has sanctioned &lt;strong&gt;₹86.27 lakh&lt;/strong&gt; for the augmentation of Community Health Centres (CHCs) and Primary Health Centres (PHCs).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Infrastructure Boost:&lt;/strong&gt; The funds will be used to provide &lt;strong&gt;ambulances, ventilators, USG machines&lt;/strong&gt;, and advanced life-support equipment to underserved tribal populations.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Organization:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;NSTFDC&lt;/strong&gt; is a Section 8 company functioning under the &lt;strong&gt;Ministry of Tribal Affairs&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Aspirational Districts Programme&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Launched by the Government of India in 2018, it aims to quickly and effectively transform districts that have shown relatively less progress in key social areas.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;NSTFDC&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The National Scheduled Tribes Finance and Development Corporation provides financial assistance for the economic development of Scheduled Tribes.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Section 8 Company&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;A company registered for charitable or non-profit objectives, where profits are applied toward promoting those objectives rather than paying dividends to members.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
